{{Orphan|date=August 2016}} '''Community respiration''' (CR) refers to the total amount of [[CO2|carbon-dioxide]] that is produced by individuals [[organisms]] in a given [[community]], originating from the [[cellular respiration]] of [[organic material]]. CR is an important [[ecological]] index as it dictates the amount of production for the higher [[trophic levels]] and influence [[biogeochemical cycles]].<ref>{{cite journal|last1=Wilson|first1=Jesse|title=Ocean-Scale Patterns in Community Respiration Rates along Continuous Transects across the Pacific Ocean|journal=PLoS One|date=2014|volume=9|issue=7|doi=10.1371/journal.pone.0099821}}</ref> CR is often used as a proxy for the [[biological activity]] of the microbial community.<ref>{{cite journal|last1=O. Hedin|first1=Lars|title=Factors Controlling Sediment Community Respiration in Woodland Stream Ecosystems|journal=Oikos|date=1990|volume= 57|issue=1|pages=94–105|doi=10.2307/3565742}}</ref>
==See also== * [[Microbial ecology]]
