===†Sauropods=== {| class="wikitable" align="center" width="100%" |- ! colspan="5" align="center" |[[Sauropoda]] of the Toarcian |- ! Taxa ! Presence ! Location ! Description ! Images |- | *''[[Barapasaurus]]'' | | Maharastra, India | Reached a length of about 18 metres (60&nbsp;feet), and weighed about 48 tones (53 tons). Its height to the hip was approximately 5.5 metres (18&nbsp;feet) | rowspan="99" |[[Image:Barapasaurus DB.jpg|thumb|center|200px|''[[Barapasaurus]]'']] |- | *''[[Rhoetosaurus]]'' | Disputed | Central Queensland, Australia | Estimated to have been about 12–15 metres long. Has been compared to Shunosaurus, based on similar general age, but without justification. |- | *''[[Tazoudasaurus]]'' | Toarcian | Ouarzazate province, Morocco | Small primitive sauropod, about 9 metres long. Member of [[Vulcanodontidae]] family.<ref name="allain04">{{Cite journal| doi = 10.1016/j.crpv.2004.03.001| issn = 1631-0683| volume = 3| issue = 3| pages = 199–208| last = Allain| first = Ronan|author2=Najat Aquesbi |author3=Jean Dejax |author4=Christian Meyer |author5=Michel Monbaron |author6=Christian Montenat |author7=Philippe Richir |author8=Mohammed Rochdy |author9=Dale Russell |author10=Philippe Taquet | title = A basal sauropod dinosaur from the Early Jurassic of Morocco| journal = Comptes Rendus Palevol| year = 2004| url = http://www.sciencedirect.com/science/article/pii/S1631068304000636}}<!--Moha M'ghari was the preparator, not one of the coauthors--></ref> |- |}
